    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
        At JKLHealthcare, we are committed to safeguarding your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information and outlines your rights in compliance with applicable laws and regulations.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information Collection</h2>
    <p>
        We collect personal data necessary for providing our services, including but not limited to:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Name, email, contact number, address, and date of birth.</li>
            <li><strong>Service Information:</strong> Appointment details, caregiver assignments, and feedback.</li>
            <li><strong>Technical Information:</strong> IP addresses, device identifiers, and browsing history (for security and analytics purposes).</li>
        </ul>
        We ensure that all data collection is done with your explicit consent and processed lawfully, as outlined in the <em>Data Protection Act 2018</em> and <em>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</em>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Use of Information</h2>
    <p>
        We use the information you provide for:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Service Delivery:</strong> Account creation, authentication, and appointment management.</li>
            <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Reminders, updates, and responses to inquiries.</li>
            <li><strong>Service Improvement:</strong> Enhancing system security, user experience, and quality of care.</li>
        </ul>
        All personal data is processed in accordance with GDPR principles:
        <ul>
            <li>Processed fairly, lawfully, and transparently.</li>
            <li>Collected for specified, explicit purposes.</li>
            <li>Kept secure and up-to-date.</li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>3. Data Protection</h2>
    <p>
        We implement advanced security measures, including:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> All data transmissions are encrypted using SSL/TLS.</li>
            <li><strong>Data Minimisation:</strong> Only necessary data is stored, and passwords are securely hashed.</li>
            <li><strong>Regular Audits:</strong> Routine checks ensure compliance with the <em>Computer Misuse Act 1990</em> and the <em>Network and Information Systems (NIS) Directive</em>.</li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>
    <p>
        We do not share your personal information with third parties except:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>For Legal Compliance:</strong> When required by law (e.g., <em>Investigatory Powers Act 2016</em>).</li>
            <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong> For specific services or referrals.</li>
        </ul>
        Any data transfer outside the UK adheres to the <em>EU-US Data Privacy Framework</em> for cross-border data security.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Access and Control Over Your Information</h2>
    <p>
        As per GDPR, you have the right to:
        <ul>
            <li>Access your data.</li>
            <li>Request corrections or deletion of data.</li>
            <li>Restrict or object to data processing.</li>
            <li>Transfer your data (data portability).</li>
        </ul>
        Contact us at <a href="mailto:customer.service@jklhealthcare.com">customer.service@jklhealthcare.com</a> to exercise your rights.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Legal Compliance</h2>
    <p>
        Our platform complies with the following laws and regulations:
        <ul>
            <li><em>Data Protection Act 2018 & GDPR:</em> Ensures personal data is processed lawfully and securely.</li>
            <li><em>Computer Misuse Act 1990:</em> Prevents unauthorized access to systems and data.</li>
            <li><em>Telecommunications (Security) Act 2021:</em> Secures communications and infrastructure.</li>
            <li><em>Investigatory Powers Act 2016:</em> Regulates data interception and access.</li>
            <li><em>European Human Rights Act:</em> Protects your right to privacy.</li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>7. Changes to the Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
        This policy may be updated periodically to reflect new legal requirements or enhancements to our services. We encourage you to review it regularly.
    </p>

    <p>
        For further information or concerns, please reach out to <a href="mailto:customer.service@jklhealthcare.com">customer.service@jklhealthcare.com</a>.
    </p>
